Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. (Cases 22CF694, 22CF1205 are called at 11:21 AM- by Zoom) Defendant Hailey Seim appears in custody via video conference from the Jail with Attorney Sonia Anderson. Attorney George Miller appears separately by video. ADA Kelly Ronquist appears in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Warrant in 22CF694 is executed. Court advises Defendant of charges in 22CF694, 22CF1205. Defense Attorney Miller waives reading of the criminal complaints in 22CF694, 22CF1205. Defendant updates address and phone number. State requests $1,000 cash bond- recites failures to appear. Defense Attorney Miller requests signature bond or lower cash bond. Time limits for preliminary hearing waived. Court orders $200 cash bond with various conditions.
